{"primary_role": "CEO and President @ HipLogic", "updated": "2017-07-08T14:50:08", "jobs": [{"title": "CEO and President", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/hiplogic", "company": "HipLogic", "started_on": "Apr, 2008", "is_current": "false", "ended_on": "Aug, 2012"}], "description": "Mark Anderson is a Mobile Veteran and Entrepreneur with experience ranging from Start-Up CEO to Public Company Executive. Mark is currently VP of Business and Corporate Development at SnapOne Inc., responsible for Key Business Partnerships, Acquisitions and Strategy. Before joining SnapOne, Mark was the Head of Mobile Advertising at Zynga and was responsible for generating and scaling advertising revenues for Zynga's Mobile Games business in addition to executing on International mobile distribution with OEMs and global carrier groups. Mark was Chief Executive Officer and President of HipLogic Inc., a Mobile Social Multimedia platform that leverages Social Networking and Consumer Media Brands where he grew the company and led the acquisition by Zynga. Mark has over 20 years of Mobile, Internet and Advertising experience. Anderson served as Vice President, Internet and Media Solutions at Ericsson where he led the expansion of Ericsson\u2019s business with Internet and Media companies including strategic consulting efforts with Google on their Android and 700MHz mobile initiatives. Mark Joined Ericsson in 2003 as Vice President and GM, Enterprise Business Solutions. Prior to Ericsson, he was Vice President of Sales at Vialto Corporation, a Voice XML solution provider leading up to its acquisition by Cisco Systems. Mark also held VP of Sales and Business Development roles at Air2Web (Velti) and Superscape (Glu Mobile). Mark was an early management employee at Polycom Inc. through their Initial Public Offering following his early career in advertising with GTE (YP) and Ketchum. Mark received his B.A. in Advertising from San Jose State University and has completed Corporate Executive Business Programs from Duke University\u2019s Fuqua School of Business and UCLA\u2019s Anderson School of Management.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/mark-anderson-5", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-07-08T14:50:08", "websites": [{"url": "http://twitter.com/Mobiax", "type": "twitter"}], "name": "Mark Anderson", "_key": "00857aea1486da12", "location": "Unknown", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1397184864/c21b5ef351a96c0d940839adfcb1db81.jpg", "total_jobs_count": "1"}
