{"primary_role": "Managing Director @ Spaulding & Slye Investments", "updated": "2017-08-10T19:00:56", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/spaulding-slye-investments", "company": "Spaulding & Slye Investments", "is_current": "true", "title": "Managing Director"}], "description": "Brooks joined Spaulding & Slye Investments in July 2013 as Managing Director. He is responsible for sourcing new investment opportunities and capital sources. He comes from over 13 years of experience in acquisitions, development, portfolio underwriting, investment and asset management. Experience Brooks comes to Spaulding & Slye Investments from 1788 Holdings, a local Washington, DC development and investment firm. He helped to found the company in 2010, and was responsible for sourcing acquisitions and managing all due diligence and pre-development activities. Prior to 1788 Holdings, Mr. Bossle spent more than 10 years at Archon Group, a wholly owned subsidiary of Goldman, Sachs & Co. Mr. Bossle joined Archon in 2000 to focus on a broad array of acquisition pursuits ranging from multi-billion dollar portfolios to one-off office and retail transactions. He was promoted to Director of Acquisitions in 2007 to oversee Retail Acquisitions in the Mid-Atlantic where he acquired, developed, managed and disposed of properties worth approximately $200 million in the Washington, DC area and Richmond. Additionally, he played a significant role in the underwriting and pursuit of Goldman Sachs\u2019 large portfolio acquisition initiatives, including the oversight of all retail underwriting. In this capacity, Mr. Bossle designed the scope of the due diligence and managed underwriting teams to value complex portfolios under a compressed timeline. This experience allowed him to personally underwrite multi-billion dollars of office, industrial and retail properties in many markets throughout the country as well as build relationships with a large national network.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/brooks-bossle", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-08-10T19:00:56", "name": "Brooks Bossle", "_key": "422bd7269607e43a", "total_jobs_count": "1", "images": "/assets/default_image_cb-e2471225359df18a02957cad1c97c684.png", "location": "Unknown"}
{"primary_role": "Vice President Of Global Human Resources & Chief Compliance Officer @ St. Jude Medical", "updated": "2017-08-27T10:20:38", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/st-jude-medical", "company": "St. Jude Medical", "is_current": "true", "title": "Vice President Of Global Human Resources & Chief Compliance Officer"}], "description": "With St. Jude Medical since 2003. Paul Bae was named vice president of global human resources in February 2015, adding this role\u2019s duties to those of chief compliance officer. He joined St. Jude Medical in 2003 and was named deputy general counsel, labor and employment and chief compliance officer in 2012. Mr. Bae has extensive experience in labor and employment law, and previously served St. Jude Medical as vice president, corporate HR from 2006 to 2009 and as senior vice president, administration and general counsel for what is now the Americas division from 2009 to 2012. Prior to joining St. Jude Medical, Mr. Bae was a prosecutor in Silicon Valley and a litigator for the San Francisco and Los Angeles offices of the law firm of Ropers, Majeski, Kohn & Bentley. He also headed the litigation team of Alpha Therapeutic Corporation, a biopharmaceutical company. Mr. Bae received bachelor\u2019s degrees in political science and sociology from University of California, Los Angeles, and has a law degree from the University of the Pacific, McGeorge School of Law.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/paul-bae", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-08-27T10:20:38", "name": "Paul Bae", "_key": "9e13a6d3f1ecb5c4", "total_jobs_count": "1", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1461848127/pgns81sfmargtdnyab1c.png", "location": "Unknown"}
