on and acquisition of silver stream opportunities. In January 2010 he was appointed President, and in April 2011 he was appointed Silver Wheaton's Chief Executive Officer. Smallwood originally started as an exploration geologist with Wheaton River Minerals Ltd., and in 2001 was promoted to Director of Project Development, his role through its 2005 merger with Goldcorp. Before joining the original Wheaton River group in 1993, Smallwood also worked with Homestake Mining Company, Teck Corp. and Westmin Resources. Smallwood was an instrumental part of the team that built Wheaton River / Goldcorp into one of the largest, and more importantly most profitable gold companies in the world, and is now focused on continuing to add to the impressive growth profile of Silver Wheaton.", "total_jobs_count": "8", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1452013241/plimcav5utzddovjp1gw.jpg", "total_events_count": "1", "primary_role": "President @ Silver Wheaton", "name": "Randy Smallwood", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/randy-smallwood", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-08-15T01:57:51", "websites": [{"url": "https://ca.linkedin.com/in/randy-smallwood-39092b17", "type": "linkedin"}], "_key": "a230d5c0fc0da34e", "location": "Vancouver", "events_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/person/randy-smallwood/events"], "events": [{"name": "Mines and Money Americas 2017", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/event/mines-and-money-americas-2017-2017102", "image": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_100,w_100/v1487162872/mi4n81j3tsn4pyy4gjlp.png", "source_url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/randy-smallwood/events", "role": "Speaker", "date": "October  2, 2017 - October  4, 2017", "description": "Mines and Money is the leading international event series for mining investment and capital raising."}]}
