{"updated": "2017-08-13T16:13:36", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/spinal-kinetics", "company": "Spinal Kinetics", "is_current": "true", "title": "Founder, CEO, President & Director"}], "description": "Tom Afzal is the President, CEO, co-Founder and a Director of Spinal Kinetics, a company that developed and is commercializing total artificial discs for the spine. Previously, he was the Founder, President and CEO of CardioVention, a company that developed a minimal invasive bypass system used in cardiac surgery. Previously he was General Manager of the Cardiac Valve Group and also served as Vice President, Sales and Marketing at CardioThoracic Systems (CTS), the pioneer and leader in minimally invasive beating heart surgery, acquired by Guidant Corp. in 1999. Prior to CTS, he was President of Krauth Medical, one of Europe\u2019s largest medical device companies, and where he also served as a member of the Board of Directors. He was the Founder and President of Life Systems, a European based service provider of combined personnel and products to cardiac surgery and cardiology catheter-lab suites which was later integrated into the Krauth Medical group of companies. Earlier he held various upper management positions in marketing, sales and international management at SulzerMedica (orthopedic and cardiovascular groups), Baxter Healthcare and American Hospital Supply Corp. He has raised over $140 million in capital for start-ups. He is also named on over 30 issued or pending patents. He serves on the board of a number of medical device companies and also served on the board of SDSU College of Business. He is also a co-founder of Heart Repair Technologies, a company developing unique system to treat heart valve diseases. He received his BS in Business from San Diego State University.", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1429791805/dwsleikybmojrkanblph.png", "total_boards_and_advisor_roles_