{"updated": "2017-08-24T05:14:45", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/los-angeles-business-journal", "company": "Los Angeles Business Journal", "is_current": "true", "period": "1994 - Current (over 23 years)", "title": "CEO & Publisher"}], "description": "Matthew Toledo is Publisher and Chief Executive Officer of the Los Angeles Business Journal, the largest regional business media company in California. Matthew oversees all editorial, advertising, circulation and strategic planning for the publication. Matthew is also Group Publisher of California Business Journals; which owns and operates the Orange County Business Journal, San Diego Business Journal and the San Fernando Valley Business Journal. Under Matthew's direction, the Los Angeles Business Journal has been recognized as the best regional business journal in the country for its compelling coverage and quality journalism. In addition to leading the Business Journal for the past 20 years, Matthew is a passionate civic leader; serving on numerous boards as a director and advisor. Matthew is on the Boards of Directors of the Los Angeles Chamber of Commerce, where he served as Chair, the Los Angeles Economic Development Corporation, the Los Angeles Sports and Entertainment Commission, United Way of Greater LA, Civic Alliance, and Town Hall Los Angeles. In addition, Matthew is on the Executive Committee of the Central City Association. Matthew also serves as a Member of the Board of Directors at Greenwood Hall. Matthew formerly served as Member of the Board of Directors at Los Angeles Police Foundation, Operation Hope, Junior Achievement, Center for Nonprofit Management, and Alliance of Area Business Publications where he also served as Chairman. Matthew was on the Board of Visitors for Pepperdine University George L. Graziadio School of Business and Management. Originally from Chicago and raised in Northern California, Matthew is a graduate of San Jose State University with a Bachelor of Ar