{"updated": "2017-08-12T11:45:12", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/omegawave", "company": "Omegawave", "is_current": "true", "title": "Co-Founder & Vice President of Business Development"}], "description": "Omegawave's co-founder and Vice President of Business Development, Ukrainian-born Val Nasedkin has always focused on adapting the technology to the needs of coaches and trainers. When I founded Omegawave, I was also doing a lot of coaches counseling for different sport organizations and I saw how coaches were always looking for better training solutions. Being a coach and a former track and field athlete myself \u2013 as well as an expert in physiological readiness.I wanted to use my expertise to help create those new training solutions. As Val puts it, Omegawave\u2019s approach is different than other sports applications on the market that just measure what you\u2019re doing or what you\u2019ve done. Instead of a simple measurement, Omegawave shows you whether the training you did was good or bad for your body \u2013 and then offers advice on better ways to train. It really motivates me to see how our technology has helped so many coaches to become better and guided so many athletes to reach a higher level. With the new mobile application, Val sees Omegawave positioned to be of value in any situation where people have to deal with stress. But the basic principle, the overall concept, remains the same. As long as we can contribute to someone\u2019s health and performance, this is valuable. Only the challenges are different: for elite athletes it may mean winning gold, for someone else it may be running 10 kilometers or just staying in better shape. Val also praises Finland as a great location for Omegawave. In addition to the government support for innovative business, Val appreciates the very high concentration of well-educated and highly skilled people available to provide their services at a reasonable price. At Omegawave, we\u2019re still full of ideas and don\u2019t plan to stop where we are right now. Though the business keeps me busy, every time I have an opportunity I enjoy cycling, running and rollerblading. And when I happen to watch TV, I prefer track and field sports, the Olympic games and World Cup Soccer.", "total_jobs_count": "1", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1397184964/9fdd77ffe9de0e858de49a3b5d7aac4e.jpg", "news": [{"date": "Oct 13, 2014", "article": {"url": "http://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2014-10-13/under-armour-holds-a-game-show-to-find-its-future", "publisher": "bloomberg.com", "uuid": "f8c0b8e8f0ca46df80c9ecc0666f499b", "title": "Under Armour Holds a Game Show to Find Its Future"}, "publication": "Bloomberg", "source_url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/val-nasedkin/press"}], "primary_role": "Co-Founder & Vice President of Business Development @ Omegawave", "news_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/person/val-nasedkin/press"], "name": "Val Nasedkin", "total_news_count": "1", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-07-09T07:49:27", "websites": [{"url": "http://fi.linkedin.com/pub/val-nasedkin/82/72/505", "type": "linkedin"}], "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/val-nasedkin", "location": "Portland", "_key": "62a43b8004186ed6"}
