{"primary_role": "CEO @ Lumenogix", "updated": "2017-08-26T16:48:19", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/lumenogix", "company": "Lumenogix", "is_current": "true", "title": "CEO"}], "description": "Dr. Umylny has an undergraduate degree in Computer Science from Columbia University, and a PhD in Cell and Molecular Biology from the University of Hawaii. Professionally, Dr. Umylny has more than twenty years of hands-on expertise developing, selling, integrating, using, and maintaining complex enterprise software \u2013 initially for financial firms, and more recently (with Lumenogix) \u2013 for genomic and related science research. In 1992 Dr. Umylny co-founded Fusion Systems Japan, a Tokyo-based consulting and software development company specializing in financial systems development and integration for which he served as Vice President until selling the firm via an M&A transaction in 1999. In this capacity, Dr. Umylny was responsible for all development and deployment of electronic trading and order execution platforms where he also oversaw and managed integrations for most of the major brokerage firms operating in Asia, including Jardine Fleming, Deutsche Bank, Morgan Stanley, Paribas, First Boston, Credit Suisse, UBS, and Hitachi among many others.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/boris-umylny", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-08-26T16:48:19", "websites": [{"url": "http://www.linkedin.com/in/borisumylny/en", "type": "linkedin"}], "name": "Boris Umylny", "_key": "3b4ed6897d86cafa", "location": "Santa Fe", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1426054716/jcngcmx272mj14hid4bk.png", "total_jobs_count": "1"}
{"updated": "2017-08-12T02:19:54", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/keybank", "company": "Keybank", "is_current": "true", "title": "President, Key Corporate Bank"}], "description": "Christopher M. Gorman is Chairman and CEO of KeyBank, NA and President of Key Corporate Bank, which includes KeyBank Real Estate Capital, Enterprise Commercial Payments, Key Equipment Finance and KeyBanc Capital Markets. Additionally, Mr. Gorman is a member of KeyCorp's Executive Council, Management Committee, and President, Key Foundation Board of Trustees. Previously, he served as President of KeyBanc Capital Markets and was responsible for KeyCorp's Corporate, Investment Banking and Capital Markets businesses. Prior to that, he served as Executive Vice President and Head of Corporate Banking. Mr. Gorman also served as Senior Managing Director and Deputy Director of Investment Banking for McDonald Investments Inc., a registered broker-dealer acquired by KeyCorp in 1998. Prior to his tenure at Key, Mr. Gorman held various roles in the Corporate Finance department at Bankers Trust Company. Mr. Gorman is the Chairman of the Board of Business Volunteers Unlimited. He serves on the Sisters of Charity Health System Executive Committee and Board of Directors. He also serves on the Board of Team NEO. Mr. Gorman is a member of The Financial Services Roundtable. Mr. Gorman graduated from Miami University in 1983 with a Bachelor's Degree in Finance. He currently serves as Chairman of the Business Advisory Council of Miami University\u2019s Farmer School of Business.", "images": "/assets/default_image_cb-e2471225359df18a02957cad1c97c684.png", "education_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/person/christopher-m-gorman/education"], "total_jobs_count": "1", "total_education_count": "1", "news": [{"date": "Oct 30, 2015", "article": {"url": "http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/keycorp-to-acquire-first-niagara-financial-group-300169466.html", "publisher": "prnewswire.com", "u