{"updated": "2017-08-13T15:00:42", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/mitra-biotech", "company": "Mitra Biotech", "is_current": "true", "title": "Co-Founder & CSO"}, {"title": "Research Fellow", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/merck-research-laboratories", "company": "Merck Research Laboratories", "started_on": "Unknown", "ended_on": "Unknown", "is_current": "false"}, {"title": "Member of Faculty of Medicine", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/harvard-medical-school", "company": "Harvard Medical School", "started_on": "Unknown", "ended_on": "Unknown", "is_current": "false"}, {"title": "Principal Investigator", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/ontario-institute-for-cancer-research", "company": "Ontario Institute for Cancer Research", "started_on": "Unknown", "ended_on": "Unknown", "is_current": "false"}], "description": "Dr. Pradip K. Majumder is a young entrepreneur and a co-founder of Mitra Biotech Pvt. Ltd, a Harvard-MIT spinoff biotech company dedicated for personalized cancer medicine. Pradip is the Chief Scientific Officer and member of board of directors at Mitra. He is a visiting faculty of Dana Farber Cancer Institute, Harvard Medical School, Boston. His team is identifying biomarkers and novel technologies to stratify patients for anti-cancer agents and also identifying and validating novel cancer targets. Prior to joining Mitra, Pradip was a member of Faculty of Medicine at Harvard Medical School, Boston, Research Fellow at Merck Research Laboratories, Boston and Principal Investigator of Ontario Institute for Cancer Research, Toronto. He made a significant progress in dissecting the role of two major signaling pathways (PI3K/RTK and Notch) on tumor dependency in both solid and liquid tumors. Pradip received his Ph.D. in cancer biology from All India Institute of Medical Sciences, New Delhi, India and postdoctoral research fellowship in Dana Farber Cancer Institute-Boston. He is an establi