{"updated": "2017-08-18T15:26:56", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/zyvex", "company": "Zyvex", "is_current": "true", "title": "Founder, Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and Member of the Advisory Board"}, {"title": "Co-Founder", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/texas-nanotechnology-initiative", "company": "Texas Nanotechnology Initiative", "started_on": "2000", "is_current": "false", "ended_on": "Unknown"}], "description": "Mr. James R. Von Ehr, II serves as the Founder, Chief Executive Officer, and Chairman of Zyvex Corporaton. He is personally contributing $2.5 million to UTD to set up their Nanotech Center. Mr. Von Ehr also manages the Von Ehr Foundation that he established in 1999. He is also a Co-Founder of the Feynman Grand Prize and Texas Nanotechnology Initiative, where he also serves as a Director. Before founding Zyvex in 1997, Mr. Von Ehr was the Founder, President, Chief Executive Officer, and Chairman of Altsys Corporation. He built the company from a small programming project to a major player in the desktop publishing industry. Mr. Von Ehr's team spent ten years developing several major software products including FreeHand and Fontographer. After Altsys was sold to Macromedia in 1995, he remained actively involved in programming, design, and management. Mr. Von Ehr currently serves on the Board of Directors of STARTech Early Ventures, Metroplex Technology Business Council, the North Texas Technology Council, Molecular Electronics Corporation, and NanoBusiness Alliance. He also held a seat on the Macromedia Board of Directors for nearly four years. Mr. Von Ehr is a Guest Professor of Physics at Jilin University in Changchun, China. He holds an M.S. in Mathematical Science from the University of Texas at Dallas and a B.S. in Computer Science from Michigan State University.", "total_boards_and_advisor_roles_count": "2", "total_jobs_count": "2", "boards_and_advisor_roles_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/person/