{"primary_role": "Vice President of Research @ Kolltan Pharmaceuticals", "updated": "2017-08-12T20:01:21", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/american-society-of-clinical-oncology", "company": "American Society of Clinical Oncology", "is_current": "true", "title": "Member"}, {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/american-association-for-cancer-research", "company": "American Association for Cancer Research", "is_current": "true", "title": "Member"}, {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/kolltan-pharmaceuticals", "company": "Kolltan Pharmaceuticals", "is_current": "true", "period": "2008 - Current (over 9 years)", "title": "Vice President of Research"}, {"title": "Director of the Cell Biology Department", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/imclone-systems", "company": "Imclone Systems", "started_on": "Unknown", "is_current": "false", "ended_on": "Unknown"}], "description": "Yaron Hadari, Vice President of Research, joined Kolltan in 2008. Dr. Hadari brings to Kolltan extensive experience in the discovery and development of mAbs. Prior to joining Kolltan, Dr. Hadari was the senior director of the Cell Biology Department at ImClone Systems, Inc. At ImClone, he oversaw several early- and late-stage projects aimed at developing monoclonal antibodies as anti-cancer therapies. During his academic career, Dr. Hadari focused his research on the important biological role of receptor tyrosine kinases and their downstream signal transduction pathways. Dr. Hadari received his Ph.D. degree from the Department of Molecular Cell Biology at the Weizmann Institute of Science, Rehovot, Israel, where he studied and characterized the insulin receptor signal transduction pathways. Thereafter, Dr. Hadari joined the laboratory of Dr. Joseph Schlessinger in the Pharmacology Department of New York University Langone Medical Center. At NYU, Dr. Hadari studied the biological role of select receptor tyrosine kinases in cancer and development. In addition to Dr. Hadari's Ph.D., he also holds a M.Sc. degree from the Department of Chemical Immunology at the Weizmann Institute of Science, Rehovot, Israel, and a B.Sc. degree from the Hebrew University, Jerusalem, Israel. Dr. Hadari is a member of the American Association for Cancer Research (AACR) as well as the American Society of Clinical Oncology (ASCO).", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/yaron-hadari", "gender": "Male", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1397182561/50ad6828743b26d6b7a10234ee26cbd2.jpg", "last_visited": "2017-07-08T01:38:11", "name": "Yaron Hadari", "education_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/person/yaron-hadari/education"], "location": "Unknown", "total_education_count": "3", "education": [{"organization": {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/weizmann-institute-of-science-2", "follower_count": "0", "image": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1475819778/filtypd4yneseqrmxkby.png", "name": "Weizmann Institute of Science", "uuid": "441d1da0fe67f2478dc63adccfc09a34"}, "source_url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/yaron-hadari/education", "title": "M.Sc., Department of Chemical Immunology"}, {"organization": {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/hebrew-university-of-jerusalem", "follower_count": "0", "image": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1406472672/nnnzayzasxm39aqpwrvc.png", "name": "Hebrew University of Jerusalem", "uuid": "a27f8f6c397049df7535037bac724ffc"}, "source_url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/yaron-hadari/education", "title": "BSc"}, {"organization": {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/weizmann-institute-of-science-2", "follower_count": "0", "image": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1475819778/filtypd4yneseqrmxkby.png", "name": "Weizmann Institute of Science", "uuid": "441d1da