{"primary_role": "Principal @ Vertexcs", "updated": "2017-07-08T06:37:08", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/vertexcs", "company": "Vertexcs", "is_current": "true", "title": "Principal"}], "description": "Venkit Raman, a.k.a. Venky Raman a.k.a. Venky, just like his many names, plays several roles at Vertex. As the CEO, he is constantly looking to increase value to our customers, create niche technology practice areas, and of course grow our customer base. He brings to table over 25 years of business and management experience. Prior to joining Vertex, he worked as the CIO and Country Manager for a Tokyo based Telecom Service provider. Life away from Work: Watching and playing tennis with his son and buddies, listening to classical music, and spending time with his family are his next top things to do when he is not working.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/venkit-raman", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-07-08T06:37:08", "websites": [{"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/venkit-raman-7176651a/", "type": "linkedin"}], "name": "Venkit Raman", "_key": "d5517d31c6037179", "location": "Boston", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1496834131/bhkzb01yavu4kymdqkl4.png", "total_jobs_count": "1"}
{"primary_role": "Chief Scientific Officer @ Vapogenix", "updated": "2017-07-09T09:21:52", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/vapogenix", "company": "Vapogenix", "is_current": "true", "title": "Chief Scientific Officer"}], "description": "Dr. Giles has held international leadership positions in large and small pharmaceutical companies, and her wide experience spans drug discovery and development from target validation, through clinical studies to final regulatory submission. She has a track-record of creating sustainable R&D portfolios and delivering new drugs into development and on to market. She has expertise in numerous therapeutic areas including respiratory, inflammation, pain and cardiovascular and is a respected pharmacologist with international recognition in the field of receptor theory and GPCRs. Dr. Giles joined Vapogenix in 2009 and has provided scientific and drug development leadership, which resulted in successful completion of the company\u2019s first clinical study in 2014. Previously, from 2001 to 2008, she was Vice-President of Strategic Planning at Encysive, a small pharmaceutical company in Houston, Texas. There she managed the R&D portfolio and played a pivotal role in delivering the company\u2019s key development project, Thelin, to regulatory submission and subsequent European commercial launch. Thelin is an endothelin A receptor antagonist for treatment of pulmonary arterial hypertension. Prior to Encysive, Dr. Giles was International Disease Strategy Director for Asthma at GlaxoSmithKline R&D and prior to this was Head of the Receptor Pharmacology department at GlaxoWellcome R&D, UK (1995-2000). From 1983-1995, at Wellcome R&D, UK, she held various research, project leader and management positions, with particular focus on G-protein-coupled receptors and integrins and their role in cardiovascular disease. She has an extensive scientific publication record and currently serves as adjunct Associate Professor in the Department of Pharmacology at the University of Houston. She is a member of the British Pharmacological Society and has served on their governing council and is an Editor for the British Journal of Pharmacology.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/heather-giles", "gender": "Female", "last_visited": "2017-07-09T09:21:52", "websites": [{"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/pub/heather-giles-phd-fbpharmacols/a/34a/410", "type": "linkedin"}], "name": "Heather Giles", "_key": "7bb6af1a48be82fb", "location": "Houston", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1444123803/uzeajixoztd9c6wyiuuc.png", "total_jobs_count": "1"}
