{"primary_role": "Managing Director - San Francisco @ Robert Walters", "updated": "2017-07-08T05:13:12", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/robert-walters-2", "company": "Robert Walters", "is_current": "true", "period": "2003 - Current (over 14 years)", "title": "Managing Director - San Francisco"}], "description": "Simon Bromwell moved from Tokyo to San Francisco in January of 2012 to open the United States\u2019 west coast division of Robert Walters. In less than two years, he has built an incredibly successful team and extensive network from the ground. The team has grown so much that they relocated to a larger office space earlier this summer. Simon specializes in the recruitment of mid-senior level candidates for roles in the tech sector. Prior to starting the San Francisco office, Simon headed up the highly successful Commerce Division at Robert Walters Japan. Here he was instrumental in expanding the scope of the division to include sales & marketing, HR, legal & support, and supply chain recruitment. As the Commerce Division Director, Simon was responsible for the largest single standing practice within the Robert Walters global business (ten teams and 60+ people). Before he joined Robert Walters Japan, Simon worked for a Hong Kong-based boutique executive search firm that focused exclusively on senior management recruitment. He has also worked as a Coordinator of International Relations for a local government body in Southern Japan. Simon Bromwell hails from near Liverpool in the UK. He holds a Master of Arts in Japanese Studies from the University of Edinburgh. Before making the move to the US, Simon lived and worked in Japan for nearly 10 years and is fluent in Japanese. He is a keen sportsman and plays regularly for a local recreational football team.", "url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/person/simon-bromwell", "gender": "Male", "last_visited": "2017-07-08T05:13:12", "websites": [{"url": "http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=3159481", "type": "linkedin"}], "name": "Simon Bromwell", "_key": "2bfd87b3572d0798", "location": "San Francisco", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1409689052/dlkpcmvreyvxkrabwnyu.jpg", "total_jobs_count": "1"}
{"updated": "2017-07-11T12:34:42", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/biostar-private-equity", "company": "BioStar Ventures", "is_current": "true", "title": "Managing Director"}], "description": "Dr. Cannon is a former Judith Volkman Scholar In Residence, and is the Founder and Senior Managing Director of BioStar Ventures. He has been repeatedly honored as one of \"America\u2019s Top Interventional Cardiologists\u201d, is the President of the Cardiac and Vascular Research Center of Northern Michigan, and has over hundreds of medical publications, as well as United States medical device patents. He has or does serve on the strategic advisory boards for such Fortune 500 companies as Medtronic, Abbott, and Boston Scientific, JNJ, Covidien, as well as many early developing medical technologies. He currently serves on the Board of Directors of CardioVascular Ingenuity and Kona. Dr. Cannon, through BioStar, has participated in the start up and subsequent development of a multitude of developing bio-technological, or emerging healthcare companies and has served as the National or International Principal Investigator for landmark cardiovascular studies. Dr. Cannon assisted in performing First-In-Man percutaneous Aortic Valve procedures in Paraguay in 2007 and served as Chairman of the Board of AorTx, Inc, which was successfully acquired by a publicly traded company. Similarly, BioStar was also the lead investor of Setagon, whereby Dr. Cannon served as the Chairman of the Scientific Advisory Board, which was also acquired by a Fortune 100 company.", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1397189408/e7e1b3f3feddf1fc9c5a523864211995.jpg", "total_boards_and_advisor_roles_count": "5", "total_jobs_count": "1", "boards_and_advisor_roles_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/person/louis-cannon/advisory-roles"], "total_education_count": "2", "news": [{"date": "Jul 9, 2015", "article": {"url": "http://www.fins