{"updated": "2015-12-23T03:53:52", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/covington-burling-llp", "company": "Covington & Burling LLP", "is_current": "true", "title": "Partner in the Brussels office"}, {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/university-of-rwanda", "company": "University of Rwanda", "is_current": "true", "title": "Guest Lecturer"}, {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/covington-burling-llp", "company": "Covington & Burling LLP", "is_current": "true", "title": "Co-Chair Privacy & Data Security Practice Group"}, {"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/university-of-antwerp", "company": "University of Antwerp", "is_current": "true", "title": "Assistant Professor"}], "description": "Henriette Tielemans is a partner in the Brussels office of Covington & Burling. She practices in the areas of data privacy and data security, and European Community regulatory matters. She is co-chair of Covington\u2019s Global Privacy and Data Security practice group and regularly represents clients before the European and national data privacy authorities. She advises multinationals on all aspects of EU and international privacy and security law, including data transfer issues, binding corporate rules, electronic commerce issues, e-discovery and big data. She also appears in courts and is the counsel to Facebook in pending Belgian litigation. Tielemans is a regular speaker at privacy conferences and has written several articles on privacy. She is a member of the Board of Directors of the International Association of Privacy Professionals (IAPP) and of its European Advisory Board. She was asked by the European Commission to join the Commission\u2019s Data Protection Expert Group (GEX PD). For the past several years she has been ranked as a leading privacy practitioner by Chambers Global and Legal 500 EMEA. Tielemans is a Belgian national and member of the Brussels Bar. She holds a BA and JD degree from the University in Antwer