{"updated": "2017-07-11T07:10:34", "jobs": [{"url": "https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/rockwell-collins", "company": "Rockwell Collins", "is_current": "true", "title": "Vice President, Government Systems Strategy and Business Development"}], "description": "Brad Haselhorst is the vice president, Strategy and Business Development, Government Systems for Rockwell Collins. In this position, his responsibilities include leading the company\u2019s marketing and sales organization for Government Systems, as well as overall strategy development. He was appointed to this role in April 2016. In addition, Haselhorst will continue with site leadership responsibilities for the company\u2019s Richardson, Texas facility which includes working with all leaders at the Richardson facility to provide coordinated employee engagement activities and a unified face to the community for Rockwell Collins. Previously, he served as senior director, Sales and Business Development Operations for Government Systems since May 2013. In this role, he led the U.S. based sales team, large account management, Business Development operations staff, and overall Government Systems orders volume. Haselhorst was also senior director of VIP/Special Mission & Fighter/Bomber/Trainer Solutions, Government Systems with full responsibility for profit and loss, customer relationship management, program execution, and new business pursuits for the life cycle value stream. Haselhorst has over 19 years of service with Rockwell Collins. Haselhorst holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering from The University of Iowa, a Master of Business Administration degree from Washington University in St. Louis, MO, and a Master of Science degree in National Resource Strategy from National Defense University, Washington, D.C.", "images": "https://crunchbase-production-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_140,w_140/v1467366195/vfuom8c0iw92ldkvphtp.png", "education_urls": ["https://www.crunchbase.com/pe